57.115.  Sheriff may patrol roads and highways (third and fourth class counties). — Sheriffs in counties of the third and fourth class may:
  (1)  Regularly patrol and police all public roads and highways within the county;
  (2)  Enforce all laws designed to safeguard and protect these roads and highways;
  (3)  Report all dangerous conditions on these roads and highways to the county commission or other road or highway supervising body.
(L. 1974 H.B. 1028 § 1)
